# Assignment 2: System Patch Management

## Objective
Automate patch management using Azure Automation and reusable modules.

## Project Structure
```
modules/
  automation_account/    # Azure Automation Account module
  log_analytics/         # Log Analytics Workspace module
  update_management/     # Update Management configuration module
main.tf                  # Root configuration
variables.tf             # Input variables
terraform.tfvars         # Variable values
output.tf                # Outputs
provider.tf              # Azure provider
README.md                # This documentation
```

## Modules Overview

### log_analytics
Creates a Log Analytics Workspace for collecting logs and monitoring update compliance.
- Inputs: name, location, resource_group_name
- Outputs: workspace_id

### automation_account
Creates an Azure Automation Account and links it to the Log Analytics Workspace.
- Inputs: name, location, resource_group_name, log_analytics_workspace_id
- Outputs: automation_account_id

### update_management
Configures Update Management to register VMs for patching and schedule weekly deployments.
- Inputs: automation_account_id, vm_ids, time_zone, schedule_start_time
- Outputs: update_configuration_name

## Usage Instructions

1. Update `terraform.tfvars` with your values:
   - env: Environment name
   - schedule_start_time: Start time for weekly patches (e.g., "2026-01-01T02:00:00Z")

2. Initialize Terraform:
   ```
   terraform init
   ```

3. Plan and apply:
   ```
   terraform plan
   terraform apply
   ```

## Monitoring Patch Compliance

- Use Azure Portal: Go to Automation Account > Update Management > View compliance status
- Query logs in Log Analytics Workspace for patch deployment results
- Check outputs for configuration details

## Important: Deprecation Notice
> **Azure Automation Update Management was deprecated on 31st August 2024 and has been shut down on 28th February 2025.**
> Microsoft recommends migrating to **Azure Update Manager**.
> Learn more: https://aka.ms/mmaagentbasedservicesshutdown
>
> This assignment uses `azurerm_automation_software_update_configuration` for demonstration purposes. In production, use Azure Update Manager (`azurerm_maintenance_configuration`) instead.

## Notes
- This configuration assumes the VM is deployed via Assignment 1 in the same resource group.
- The VM name is constructed as "vm-${env}" (e.g., "vm-dev").
- Ensure VMs are in the same subscription as the Automation Account.